-- Foreign Holdings of Brazil Debt Increased to a Record 150.6 Billion Reais
-- B y   H e l d e r   M a r i n h o
-- 2010-09-23T18:39:16Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-23/foreign-holdings-of-brazil-debt-increased-to-a-record-150-6-billion-reais.html
Holdings of Brazil government
domestic debt by foreign investors rose in August to a record
150.6 billion reais or 10.06 percent of total from 141 billion
reais in July, or 9.54 percent, said Fernando Garrido, head of
the Public Debt Operations Department at the country’s Treasury.  Garrido, speaking to reporters today in Brasilia, said
there is room for a further increase in foreign holdings of
Brazil’s domestic bonds.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Helder Marinho at 
 hmarinho@bloomberg.net  